[SN]TITLE[SN]
Last journey of one migrant's family

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Hundreds of migrants face huge debts and a logistical nightmare to repatriate the bodies of loved ones who have died during perilous sea crossings to Europe.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
2 June 2016 Last updated at 14:55 BST
Mohammed Nowrouz Noori, an Afghan in his 30s, lost his wife Nilufar, his son Mohammad and baby daughter Nastaran in January on a failed crossing from Turkey to Greece.
Repatriating the bodies of his wife and son to Kabul for burial took him 12 days and left him bankrupt - he never found his daughter.
